Products API Reference

Each ServiceStack Route will be listed with it's Return Type, which Verbs (aka Methods) are allowed to be used with it, the url path for the endpoint, notes entered by the developer in the code, a summary of the purpose of the endpoint, the data that the endpoint can take in (parameters) as well as the Return Type's properties (if an object model) and an example of how to call it in TypeScript.

AdminGetProductFull
GET | Returns: ProductModel | Path: /Products/Product/Full/ID/{ID}

Get Full Product By ID

Takes in the following parameters

Name Data Type Parameter Type Required Description
ID int path Yes The identifier for the record to call.

TypeScript Example

var id: number = this.someValue1;
this.cvApi.products.AdminGetProductFull(id).then(r => {
	if (!r || !r.data) {
		// Error State
		return;
	}
	this.something = r.data;
}).catch(reason => console.error(reason));

AdminGetProductsForPortal
GET | Returns: ProductPagedResults | Path: /Products/Admin/Portal/Products

Use to get a list of products (for the current x-portal we can administrate only)

CreateFutureImport
POST | Returns: CEFActionResponse<int> | Path: /Products/FutureImport/Create

Use to create a new future import.

Takes in the following parameters

Name Data Type Parameter Type Required Description
FileName string body Yes The filename including extension. This will be joined to the relative folder path where the uploads would go automatically.

HasError bool body Yes Whether or not the import had any errors when it last ran
StatusID int body Yes Identifier for the Status of this object, required if no StatusModel present
Status StatusModel body Yes Model for Status of this object, required if no StatusID present
StatusKey string body Yes Key for the Status of this object, read-only
StatusName string body Yes Name for the Status of this object, read-only
StatusDisplayName string body Yes Display Name for the Status of this object, read-only
StatusTranslationKey string body Yes Translation Key for the Status of this object, read-only
StatusSortOrder int? body No Sort Order for the Status of this object, read-only
StoreID int? Not Set! Not Set! No ApiMember attribute! Please ask a Dev to add an [ApiMember] attribute

Description string body No Description of the object, optional, no max length and ideal for storing long HTML content
ID int body No Identifier of the object (required when submitting Updates, must be blank or 0 for Creates
CustomKey string body No Custom Key of the object, optional when not using an ERP integration, max 128 characters
Active bool body No Whether the object is active. Inactive objects are essentially 'Soft-Deleted'. Ensure you set this to true to keep the object alive!
CreatedDate string body No The original date this object was created. Not required for Creates, will be automatically set
UpdatedDate string body No The last time the object was modified. Not Required for Updates, will be automatically set
Hash long? body No The Hash of the object data points coming from Clarity Connect
SerializableAttributes SerializableAttributes body Yes A dictionary of extending Attributes for the this object

GetProductsByIDs
GET | Returns: List<ProductModel> | Path: /Products/Products/ByIDs

Provides the same results as calling GetProductByID multiple times with separate IDs. WARNING: You should not use this endpoint to get a large number of products, limit to a page size.

Takes in the following parameters

Name Data Type Parameter Type Required Description
StoreID int? query No The store the user has selected if present
BrandID int? query No The brand the user has selected if present
IsVendorAdmin bool? query No A flag indicating that this is a vendor admin request. This can only be set by the server.
VendorAdminID int? query No The identifier of the vendor which is logged in. This can only be set by the server.
IDs List<int> query Yes The identifiers of products to read out

};

GetProductsForCurrentStore
GET | Returns: ProductPagedResults | Path: /Products/CurrentStore/Products

Use to get a list of products (for the current store only)

Takes in the following parameters

UpsertProductType
POST | Returns: CEFActionResponse<int> | Path: /Products/ProductType/Upsert

Use to create a new or update an existing product type (as needed).

Takes in the following parameters

Name Data Type Parameter Type Required Description
StoreID int? Not Set! Not Set! No ApiMember attribute! Please ask a Dev to add an [ApiMember] attribute
Store StoreModel Not Set! Not Set! No ApiMember attribute! Please ask a Dev to add an [ApiMember] attribute
StoreKey string body No The Store Custom Key for objects
StoreName string body No The Store Name for objects
StoreSeoUrl string body No The Store SEO URL for objects
BrandID int? Not Set! Not Set! No ApiMember attribute! Please ask a Dev to add an [ApiMember] attribute
Brand BrandModel Not Set! Not Set! No ApiMember attribute! Please ask a Dev to add an [ApiMember] attribute
BrandKey string body No The Brand Custom Key for objects
BrandName string body No The Brand Name for objects
DisplayName string body No Display Name of the object
SortOrder int? body No Sort Order of the object
TranslationKey string body No Display Name of the object
Name string body Yes Name of the object, required, max length 128 characters
Description string body No Description of the object, optional, no max length and ideal for storing long HTML content
ID int body No Identifier of the object (required when submitting Updates, must be blank or 0 for Creates
CustomKey string body No Custom Key of the object, optional when not using an ERP integration, max 128 characters
Active bool body No Whether the object is active. Inactive objects are essentially 'Soft-Deleted'. Ensure you set this to true to keep the object alive!
CreatedDate string body No The original date this object was created. Not required for Creates, will be automatically set
UpdatedDate string body No The last time the object was modified. Not Required for Updates, will be automatically set
Hash long? body No The Hash of the object data points coming from Clarity Connect
SerializableAttributes SerializableAttributes body Yes A dictionary of extending Attributes for the this object
